      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of Oct 8 article about use of methyl bromide and pesticide's possible effects on ozone layer; article contained misspelled name (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article on Oct. 8 about methyl bromide, a pesticide that has raised concern among environmentalists, misspelled the surname of the president of the California Strawberry Commission, who said technological improvements suggest that some limited use of the chemical could be possible while still protecting the ozone layer. He is Rodger Wasson, not Wesson. (The error was pointed out in a telephone message shortly after the article appeared. This correction was delayed by a reporting oversight.)</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
